. Unlike pine savannas where reduction of hardwoods is often the target of management, intraspecific interactions (i.e. negative density dependence) likely play a greater role in successful longleaf recruitment and population demography in this sandhill assemblage. This study further highlights the utility of implementing and observing a range of fire applications when reintroducing fire to long unburned systems.},
